m_DescList: Sometimes it's hard to verbally enumerate certain things, but describing their complement is relatively easier.
For example, in daily life: When tidying up a room, if you can't clearly identify what to keep, start by deciding what clutter to discard. What remains is what you need.
<color=#3173FF>[^]</color> represents items enumerating the complement of characters.
<color=#3173FF>[^</color><color=#AB2800>123</color><color=#3173FF>]</color> matches any character that isn't "1", "2", or "3".
For instance, <color=#3173FF>[^</color><color=#AB2800>123</color><color=#3173FF>]</color> matches the following in <color=#3c3cff>012345</color>:
<color=#3c3cff>0</color><color=#666666>12345</color>
<color=#666666>0123</color><color=#3c3cff>4</color><color=#666666>5</color>
<color=#666666>01234</color><color=#3c3cff>5</color>
<color=#3173FF>[^</color><color=#AB2800>aeiou</color><color=#3173FF>]</color> matches any character that isn't "a", "e", "i", "o", or "u".
For example, <color=#3173FF>[^</color><color=#AB2800>aeiou</color><color=#3173FF>]</color> matches the following in <color=#3c3cff>Hello World</color>:
<color=#3c3cff>H</color><color=#666666>ello World</color>
<color=#666666>He</color><color=#3c3cff>l</color><color=#666666>lo World</color>
<color=#666666>Hel</color><color=#3c3cff>l</color><color=#666666>o World</color>
<color=#666666>Hello</color><color=#3c3cff>\u0020</color><color=#666666>World</color>
<color=#666666>Hello </color><color=#3c3cff>W</color><color=#666666>orld</color>
<color=#666666>Hello Wo</color><color=#3c3cff>r</color><color=#666666>ld</color>
<color=#666666>Hello Wor</color><color=#3c3cff>l</color><color=#666666>d</color>
<color=#666666>Hello Worl</color><color=#3c3cff>d</color>
<color=#666666>\u0020 represents an English half-width space. Since spaces cannot be highlighted, \u0020 is used here for clarity.</color>
Now, the goal is to match all numbers that do not begin with an even digit (0, 2, 4, 6, 8).
For 100% of the input data, the following rules apply:
1. Input data consists of either digits or non-digit characters.
2. All spaces are represented by " " (\u0020 English half-width space).
Please construct a regular expression that passes all tests on the right.
